{
  "text": "We concluded presence of a malignant lesion if it were confirmed by pathologic examination. If pathologic examination was not made, we considered malignancy based on other diagnostic examinations and follow-up imaging studies. CT, PET-CT, ultrasound, and skeletal scintigraphy were used, and malignancy was suggested if increased uptake on PET-CT correlated in location corresponding with abnormal findings on MRI or the lesions became larger during the follow-up periods or decreased in size after chemotherapy or radiation treatment [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "8473288"
